4.5.1 VAT audit on large enterprises in the Czech Republic
General
The taxation procedure for large enterprises is subject to the same rules as for other taxpayers.
The audit of large undertakings is governed by Czech Law No 337 / 1992, the "Tax and Fee Administration Act."
The Czech Ministry of Finance defines large enterprises as natural persons who have established a business or legal persons who have been established for the purpose of carrying out a business operation and whose net turnover for the tax period concerned states: income and corporate tax declaration amounts to at least CZK 2 billion.
The taxpayer is classified as a large enterprise on the basis of the turnover figure according to the declaration of income or corporate tax during the respective tax period, for the first time in 2003.
A natural or legal person shall not be conducted as a large enterprise for the purposes of VAT if, in three consecutive investment periods, its net turnover during the tax period is less than CZK 2 billion. expiry of the tax period for which the conditions were met for the first time in accordance with the tax declaration.
