5. conclusions
The cooperation between the two Courts of Auditors has proved its worth.
For example, the necessary findings on the systems applied in both countries could be obtained: in particular: • intra-Community transactions, • risk management at the us in particular with regard to the selection of risk-related transactions, • recovery of VAT receivables and • VAT audit of large enterprises.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and in the systems described above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to initiate a discussion among interested parties on what audit approaches and strategies can be used to combat fraud, e.g. in relations within and between Member States and the European Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained should encourage us administration to continue to be considered together.
6. communique
The report was drawn up in Czech, English and German and was signed by the Presidents of the Czech Court of Auditors and the Federal Court of Auditors.
